  Statements: 'setbg|0

    dialog|For years, the village where Hope lives has been
    haunted by nightmares.

    dialog|The entire population of the village has
    their sleep overrun with nightmares.

    dialog|Some residents who could not
    withstand the curse decided to leave the village, causing what was once a lively
    village to gradually become deserted and neglected.

    dialog|An orphan called
    Hope and several other villagers chose to stay for one reason or another.

    dialog|Despite
    finding no peace in his sleep, Hope stayed as he felt a sense of responsibility
    for the house and small farm left by his parents.

    delay|1.0

    setbg|1

    delay|1.0

    dialog|One
    night, amidst his nightmare, Hope dreams of a disembodied voice claiming to be
    a god named Morpheus.

    dialog|Morpheus claimed to be the God of dreams and
    the reason the curse of nightmares had befallen his village.

    dialog|Morpheus
    offers Hope a chance to lift the curse once and for all, by playing the Hymn
    of Life.

